refentry.refsect1:
&reftitle.description;
intjdtounix intjulian_day
This function will return a Unix timestamp corresponding to the Julian Day given in julian_day. The time returned is UTC.

&reftitle.parameters;
julian_day
A julian day number between 2440588 and 106751993607888 on 64bit systems, or between 2440588 and 2465443 on 32bit systems.

&reftitle.errors;


 If julian_day is outside of the allowed range,
 a ValueError is thrown.

&reftitle.changelog;





    &Version;
    &Description;





    8.0.0

     This function no longer returns &false; on failure, but raises a
     ValueError instead.




    7.3.24, 7.4.12

     The upper limit of julian_day has been extended. Previously,
     it was 2465342 regardless of the architecture.
